<body>
  <main>
    <header>
      <p class="eyebrow">DNS Pilot</p>
      <h1>Support</h1>
      <p>macOS DNS benchmarking, saved domain suites, and guided resolver setup.</p>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2>Common Help</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Results estimate the current network path. They do not claim full browser, game, or internet speed improvement.</li>
        <li>The Mac App Store build never silently changes macOS DNS. Guided Apply copies DNS servers and opens Network Settings.</li>
        <li>Store-safe Flush copies a checklist. It does not run administrator commands.</li>
        <li>Dota 2 SEA, CS2, and Riot/League targets use DNS plus TCP timing. They are not ICMP ping or in-match UDP latency.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>If all candidates fail, check VPN, firewall, captive portal, MDM, corporate DNS policy, and IPv4/IPv6 reachability.</li>
        <li>If DNS-only is inconclusive, retry with DNS + TCP.</li>
        <li>After changing DNS manually, flush DNS or reconnect, then run System DNS validation.</li>
        <li>Custom domain targets accept hostnames only: omit protocol prefixes, paths, ports, and spaces.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data</h2>
      <p>DNS Pilot stores custom DNS profiles, custom domain suites, and benchmark history locally on the Mac. The Store-safe build has no accounts, analytics, tracking, or cloud sync.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p><a href="mailto:{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}">{{SUPPORT_EMAIL}}</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>
